#First program in Arduino setup() and loop() are two basic functions
- setup() will be called automatically 

Slot 13 is connected to light internally To turn on/off the LED,please find  the below program

void setup() {
pinMode(13, OUTPUT);
}

void loop () {
  digitalWrite(13, HIGH);
  delay(1000);
  digitalWrite(13, LOW);
  delay(1000);
}

void :- No return type
int :- 2 bytes
float :- 4 bytes
char :- 1 char 256 posibilites 


Global variables
-------------------
setting up global variables outside of the loop helps to get the variables inside both functions
Examples:-

int led = 13;

void setup() {
pinMode(led, OUTPUT);
}

void loop () {
  digitalWrite(led, HIGH);
  delay(1000);
  digitalWrite(led, LOW);
  delay(1000);
}




